The President called FBI Special Agent in Charge Richard Deslauriers and Boston Police Commissioner Edward F. Davis to express his appreciation for the men and women of the Boston Field Office, Boston Police Department, and the Joint Terrorism Task Force. He praised their professionalism and bravery since Monday and commended their coordination in bringing this chapter of the tragedy to a close. The President acknowledged that there is still work to be done but thanked Deslauriers and Davis for their leadership. He assured them that law enforcement officials, the citizens of Boston, and all affected by the tragedy were in his thoughts and prayers.